The paper proposes a method for interpreting black-box prediction models, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of neural network models trained on text, image, and genomic data suggests a focus on applications in natural language processing, computer vision, and bioinformatics, which are covered by the cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.CR sub-categories. The mention of input subsets and feature selection suggests a focus on machine learning interpretability, which is covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories.
